    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Wine cellar cooling unit repair &mdash; commercial refrigeration expertise applied to residential cellars</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Wine cellar cooling units are essentially small commercial refrigeration systems &mdash; they use the same components as walk-in coolers: compressor, condenser coil, evaporator, expansion valve, and thermostat. Diagnosing them correctly requires refrigeration expertise, not just general appliance knowledge. Most LA appliance repair companies don&rsquo;t work on wine cellars. We do, and we apply the same diagnostic approach we use on commercial walk-in coolers.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first, then quote. The $89 fee covers the full assessment including checking the cooling unit, the cellar insulation, door seals, and ambient conditions. Wine cellar problems in LA are frequently caused by issues outside the cooling unit itself &mdash; a door seal that hardened in the dry climate, inadequate insulation in the equipment area, or a condenser coil clogged with the fine dust common in LA&rsquo;s dry environment. We find the actual cause before recommending any parts.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="la-block">
      <div class="la-label">&#127774; LA Climate Factors for Wine Cellars</div>
      <p>Los Angeles presents two specific wine cellar challenges. First, LA&rsquo;s dry climate (relative humidity often 20&ndash;40%) means door gaskets and cellar insulation dry out and crack faster than in humid climates &mdash; creating heat infiltration that overloads the cooling unit. Second, fine particulate dust in LA air accumulates quickly on condenser coils, restricting airflow and causing the compressor to run hot. Annual condenser cleaning is essential in LA to prevent premature compressor failure &mdash; not optional maintenance.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:32px;">
