    <p class="sl">Cost Factors</p>
    <h2>What affects wine cellar repair cost in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="factors-grid">
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127774;</div><h3>LA dust on condenser coils</h3><p>LA&rsquo;s dry, particulate-heavy air clogs condenser coils faster than almost any other US market. A coil cleaning often resolves an apparent cooling failure with no parts needed. This is the first thing we check on every wine cellar service call.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127752;</div><h3>LA dry climate and cork preservation</h3><p>LA&rsquo;s 20&ndash;40% ambient RH requires active humidification in wine cellars &mdash; passive humidity isn&rsquo;t enough. Humidity system failures in LA are more consequential than in humid climates. We check humidity systems on every cellar call.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127991;</div><h3>Cooling unit brand and age</h3><p>WhisperKool, Breezaire, and CellarCool have widely available OEM parts. Sub-Zero, EuroCave, and Liebherr use proprietary components at premium pricing. Older units may have limited parts availability &mdash; we advise upfront.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128295;</div><h3>Installation type</h3><p>Through-wall units are straightforward to access. Ducted split systems require accessing both the evaporator inside the cellar and the condensing unit outside. Custom built-in cellars may require panel removal.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#9874;</div><h3>Refrigerant handling</h3><p>Wine cellar cooling unit refrigerant work requires an EPA-certified technician. Refrigerant recharge and leak repair are quoted as separate line items from the labor &mdash; you see each cost clearly.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128204;</div><h3>Holistic diagnosis &mdash; not just the unit</h3><p>A cooling unit working perfectly but fighting a failed door seal or poor insulation will still underperform. We assess the full system &mdash; unit, seals, insulation, ambient conditions &mdash; before recommending any component replacement.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

