<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Questions about wine cellar repair costs in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does wine cellar repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor runs $240&ndash;$560 for cooling unit repairs depending on the failure. Condenser coil cleaning &mdash; the most common LA wine cellar fix &mdash; runs $180&ndash;$280 with no parts needed. Parts are quoted separately. The $89 diagnostic fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why is my wine cellar not holding temperature in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">In LA, the most common cause is a condenser coil clogged with dry-climate dust &mdash; no parts needed, just cleaning. The second most common cause is a dried-out door gasket from LA&rsquo;s low humidity. We check both before diagnosing the cooling unit itself.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">My LA wine cellar has very low humidity. Is that a problem?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes. LA&rsquo;s ambient humidity of 20&ndash;40% is too dry for wine storage without active humidification. Cork drying starts at sustained humidity below 50%. Most wine cellars in LA need a working humidifier system &mdash; we check humidity systems on every cellar service call and repair them when needed.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What wine cellar cooling unit brands do you repair in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">We repair WhisperKool, CellarCool, Breezaire, Wine Guardian, Koolspace, Sub-Zero, Liebherr, EuroCave, Perlick, U-Line, and most custom built-in wine cellar systems. For commercial-scale wine storage, we apply our walk-in cooler expertise.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; all prices on this page are labor only. Parts and refrigerant are quoted as separate line items after diagnosis. This is especially important for wine cellar repairs where compressor and refrigerant costs can vary significantly by unit type and age. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the $89 diagnostic fee?</div><div class="faq-a">We charge $89 to come out and diagnose the problem, including a full system assessment of the cooling unit, door seals, insulation, and ambient conditions. That fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work. If you decide not to repair, you pay $89 and we leave.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

